
6a. Create a variable hour and save the current hour of the day and save it as a number between 0 and 23 use 24 hour format.
- If hour is between 6 and 12 display Good morning in the console.
- If hour is between 12 and 5 display Good afternoon in the console.
- Otherwise, display Good night in the console.

6b. Contuing from 6a try changing the value in the hour variable to make it display different messages.

6c. Continuing from 6a, create a variable called name and save your name inside as a string. Update the if-statement to display your name in each message. For example: Good morning ${name}.

6d. Imagine an amusement park that has a discount for children (6 years and younger) or seniors (65 years or older).
- Create a variable age and save a persons age inside.
- Create an if-statement that checks if the person qualifies for discount. If they do, display Discount in the console. Otherwise, display No discount in the console.
- Try changing the age variable to display different messages.

6e. Continuing from exercise 6d, lets say the discount is only available if it is not a holiday. Create a variable const isHoliday = true; 
-Update the code so that in order to get a discount people must meet the age requirement and it is also not a holiday.
- Try changing the value of isHoliday to display different messages.

